message.content: An Orthetrum brunneum is a species of dragonfly found in Europe and parts of Asia. It is commonly known as the southern hawker. The body of Orthetrum brunneum is long, slender and brown in color, with prominent green eyes and clear wings. The wingspan of Orthetrum brunneum can reach up to 8 centimeters. This dragonfly species prefers to live near still and slow-moving freshwater ecosystems such as ponds and lakes. Orthetrum brunneum is known for its swift, agile, and acrobatic flying skills, making it a beautiful sight to observe in its natural habitat. Males of this species are territorial and can often be found perching on nearby objects.
